Web Scraping

PROJECT TITLE

second hand bikes Market Insights & Price Intelligence using Web Scraping and EDA

Business problem

The second-hand bike market in India lacks price transparency and standardized valuation. Buyers often overpay due to unclear price benchmarks, while sellers face difficulty setting competitive prices due to limited market intelligence. This results in inefficient price negotiation, longer selling cycles, and reduced marketplace trust.

Problem statement

Prospective buyers of second-hand bikes face the risk of overpaying due to information asymmetry and the difficulty of assessing a bike's true worth from listed prices. This project tackles this problem by deconstructing the factors that influence resale value. Through exploratory data analysis and visualisation , we provide a clear framework for buyers to identify fairly priced bikes and negotiate effectively, ensuring they get the best value for their money.

Objective

To build a data-driven pricing intelligence layer that helps determine fair and competitive resale prices for second-hand bikes across different brands, models, and regions. To provide transparency for buyers and sellers, reducing price uncertainty and negotiation dependency during transactions. To support dealers and platforms with insights that optimize inventory, predict demand, and improve conversion rates in the used bike marketplace.

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import numpy as np
import time

productname = [] 
price = []
details= []

total_time = time.time()

for i in range(1,52): 
    start_time = time.time()
    URL = f'https://bikekharido.in/used-bikes-in-india/?sf_paged={i}'
    page = requests.get(URL)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.text, "html.parser")

    for x in soup.find_all('div', attrs={'class':"fl-post-text"}):
        pname = x.find('h2', attrs={'class':"fl-post-title-old bikeListHead"})
        cost = x.find('span', attrs={'class':"fw500 spanblock fsize17 fcblack"})
        own=x.find_all('span',class_="boxlabel imptags")
        

        productname.append(pname.text if pname else np.nan)
        price.append(cost.text if cost else np.nan)
        details.append(own if own else np.nan)
        
     
    print(f'Page {i} completed in {time.time()-start_time:.2f} seconds')

print("Total Time Completed in seconds", str(time.time()-total_time))

def custom():
    global i,j,k,l,m
    i = input("Enter the brand you are searching for")
    i = i.capitalize()
    j = input("Enter your maximum budget ")
    k = input("Enter maximum Km's travelled bike you are looking for")
    l = int(input("Enter the oldest year you are looking for"))
    m = input("enter your location")
    
    try:
        print(df[(df['Brand']==i) & ( df['Price']<int(j)) & (df['Km']<int(k)) & (df['Year']>int(l))& (df['location'] == m ]))
    except(ValueError):
        pass
